Sentencas: The high interface resistance between cathodes and interconnects is a major cause for performance degradation of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: The investigation of Ag & LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-δ composites as cathode contact material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Ag particles were mixed to LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-delta (LCN) matrix which prevented the silver densification and demonstrated porosity microstructure.
Titulo: The investigation of Ag & LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-δ composites as cathode contact material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The composites with different Ag content were evaluated as cathode contact materials with SUS430 alloy as interconnects.
Titulo: The investigation of Ag & LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-δ composites as cathode contact material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area specific resistance (ASR) of SUS430/10%Ag & LCN/SUS430 showed the optimal performance in which the ASR was 73 m Omega cm(2) after 50 h at 750 degrees C and showed stable property in 10 thermal cycles from 200 degrees C to 750 degrees C.
Titulo: The investigation of Ag & LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-δ composites as cathode contact material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The excellent performance of 10%Ag & LCN is attributed to the high conductivity of silver, the stable microstructure of LCN and its good interface adhesion with the interconnect alloy.
Titulo: The investigation of Ag & LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-δ composites as cathode contact material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: With 10%Ag & LCN as cathode contact materials, the power density of a single cell reached 0.623 W/cm(2) at 750 degrees C and the average degradation is lower than 1% in 3 thermal cycles.
Titulo: The investigation of Ag & LaCo0.6Ni0.4O3-δ composites as cathode contact material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
